The paper proposes a method for hand segmentation using a novel Deep Learning architecture based on convolutional layers. This suggests that the paper is likely to belong to the Computer Vision (cs.CV) sub-category. Additionally, the paper mentions the use of multi-scale processing, which is a common technique in the fields of Artificial Intelligence (cs.AI) and Machine Learning (cs.LG). The paper also mentions the use of real-time processing, which suggests that it may be relevant to Multimedia (cs.MM) and Robotics (cs.RO) sub-categories.
